The paper deals with image colorization using deep learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of pre-trained convolutional neural networks also suggests the paper may fall under machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The application of the proposed method to ukiyo-e paintings suggests the paper may also fall under graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
